Instrument tuning details:<br /><br />(Information according to Jangler)<br /><br />each instrument has 16 possible pitchesâ€”the B1 through G3 (in b00daw's terminology) that you can normally place, as well as placeholders for A1, A3, and B3. normally these placeholders are a G2, B2, and C3 respectively, but a few instruments have notes there which are not ordinarily accessible:<br /><br />mushroom: B3 is between C3 and D3 (nonlinear)<br />yoshi: A1 is C1<br />star: A3 is Aâ™¯0, B3 is B0<br />cat: A1 is D4, B3 is B3<br />baby: A1 is G4, A3 is B3, B3 is Dâ™¯1<br />boat: A3 is very high, B3 is between E3 and F3 (nonlinear)<br />heart: A1 is C1<br /><br />and while i'm thinking about it, here are the pitches of the &quot;non-melodic&quot; instruments, ascending from B1 to G3. i'm going to use flats and sharps fairly arbitrarily here.<br /><br />the mushroom ascends in increasing intervals:<br />F Gâ™­ Aâ™­ Bâ™­ Dâ™­ F Aâ™­ B Eâ™­ Gâ™­ Dâ™­ Gâ™­ Gâ™­<br /><br />the pig is tuned a minor third higher than the rest of the instruments:<br />D Eâ™­ F G Aâ™­ Bâ™­ C D Eâ™­ G Aâ™­ Bâ™­<br />edit: today i think it sounds more like a whole step.<br />Câ™¯ D E Fâ™¯ G A B Câ™¯ D E Fâ™¯ G A<br /><br />the baby instrument plays two notes, the first of which is tuned a minor second lower than the other instruments:<br />Aâ™¯ B Câ™¯ Dâ™¯ E Fâ™¯ Gâ™¯ Aâ™¯ B Câ™¯ Dâ™¯ E Fâ™¯<br />the second note is a major sixth above the first:<br />G Aâ™­ Bâ™­ C Dâ™­ Eâ™­ F G Aâ™­ Bâ™­ C Dâ™­ Eâ™­<br /><br />boat is wacky. the first couple of cymbals sound melodic to me but the rest don't and the rest also do:<br />Dâ™¯ Fâ™¯ Gâ™¯ Aâ™¯ B Câ™¯ | Câ™¯ Fâ™¯ Câ™¯ E Gâ™¯ B D<br /><br />(yoshi is tuned about right)<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=3466">B00daW</a> â€” Mon Jun 26, 2017 7:47 pm</p><hr />
