Mariopants does not currently export SRAM format.  Mario Paint's SRAM is compressed.  HertzDevil discovered that Mario Paint's SRAM is encoded with combined LZ77 and huffman algorithms.<br /><br />Here is the LUA script for SRAM decompression:<br /><br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">#!/usr/bin/env lua5.3<br /><br />if #arg &lt; 2 then<br />Â  print &quot;Usage: lua5.3 mp_unpack.lua &lt;srm&gt; &lt;output&gt;&quot;<br />Â  os.exit()<br />end<br /><br />local f = io.open(arg&#91;1&#93;, &quot;rb&quot;)<br /><br />f:seek(&quot;set&quot;, 0x7FE)<br />local datasize = (&quot;&lt;I2&quot;):unpack(f:read(2))<br />local maptable = {}<br />for i = 1, 0x400 do<br />Â  maptable&#91;i&#93; = (&quot;&lt;I2&quot;):unpack(f:read(2))<br />end<br />local bin = {}<br />for i = 1, datasize / 2 - 0x400 do<br />Â  bin&#91;i&#93; = (&quot;&lt;I2&quot;):unpack(f:read(2))<br />end<br /><br />local lz = {}<br />local huff_ptr = 0<br />for i, v in ipairs(bin) do<br />Â  for n = 15, 0, -1 do<br />Â  Â  huff_ptr = maptable&#91;huff_ptr / 2 + (v &amp; (1 &lt;&lt; n) ~= 0 and 2 or 1)&#93;<br />Â  Â  if maptable&#91;huff_ptr / 2 + 1&#93; == 0 then<br />Â  Â  Â  table.insert(lz, maptable&#91;huff_ptr / 2 + 2&#93;)<br />Â  Â  Â  huff_ptr = 0<br />Â  Â  end<br />Â  end<br />end<br /><br />local out = {}<br />local lz_ptr = 1<br />local lz_size = #lz<br />while lz_ptr &lt; lz_size do<br />Â  local lo, hi = lz&#91;lz_ptr&#93;, lz&#91;lz_ptr + 1&#93;<br />Â  lz_ptr = lz_ptr + 2<br />Â  if hi &gt;= 0x80 then<br />Â  Â  for i = 1, hi - 0x80 do<br />Â  Â  Â  out&#91;#out + 1&#93; = out&#91;#out + 1 - lo&#93;<br />Â  Â  end<br />Â  else<br />Â  Â  for i = 1, hi * 0x100 + lo do<br />Â  Â  Â  out&#91;#out + 1&#93;, lz_ptr = lz&#91;lz_ptr&#93;, lz_ptr + 1<br />Â  Â  end<br />Â  end<br />end<br /><br />local outfile = io.open(arg&#91;2&#93;, &quot;wb&quot;)<br />outfile:write(string.char(table.unpack(out)))<br />outfile:close()<br /><br />f:close()</div><br />There is currently no script for recompression yet.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=3466">B00daW</a> â€” Mon Jun 26, 2017 7:12 pm</p><hr />
